description: First attested in  1731. Borrowed from Latin ēlūtus, from the verb ēluō (“I wash away”).

verbs.description: elute (third-person singular simple present elutes, present participle eluting, simple past and past participle eluted)

entries.meaning: (transitive) To separate one substance from another by means of a solvent; to wash; to cleanse.
examples: A mixture of isooctane and ethyl acetate can be used to elute triglycerides from a complex lipid solution.
